  \cli\out sends output to STDOUT
  It does not automatically append a new line
  It does accept any number of arguments which are then passed to sprintf for formatting
  Alternatively, you can use an array as the second argument.

  \cli\line forwards to \cli\out for output
  It does automatically append a new line
  It does accept any number of arguments which are then passed to sprintf for formatting
  Alternatively, you can use an array as the second argument.

